uk.ac.ebi.centres.priority.descriptor

Class DescriptorList

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.centres.priority.descriptor.DescriptorList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<DescriptorList>

    public final class DescriptorList
extends Object
implements Comparable<DescriptorList>
    Implementation of a descriptor list that allows descriptors to be added and ignored. The list maintains an integer value throughout which stores the pairing of descriptors and allows easy comparison between descriptor lists in that higher priority descriptor pairing will always have a higher integer value. The integer value can be access via the getPairing() method.
    Author:
    John May

      • DescriptorList

        public DescriptorList(DescriptorList head,
                      DescriptorList tail)
        Creates a new list from a provided head and tail. The head and tail ignored descriptors are first transferred and then their descriptors. In either list, descriptors that are ignored by the other will be not be added to the new instance.
        Parameters:
        head - the head of the list (prefix)
        tail - the tail of the list (suffix)

      • getPairing

        public int getPairing()
        Access a positive integer that represents the like/unlike pairings of this descriptor list. The like/unlike is represented by set bits in an integer value and means larger integer values indicates a higher descriptor pairing preference.
        Returns:
        an integer representing the descriptor pairings

      • append

        public List<DescriptorList> append(Collection<? extends DescriptorList> lists)
        Appends multiple descriptor lists. If more then one list is provided the head (this list) is duplicate across the multiple tails (provided). If the contents of this list is 'RRSS' and we invoke append with two lists 'SRS' and 'RSR'. Two new lists will be returned with their contents 'RRSSSRS' and 'RRSSRSR' respectively.

        Empty descriptor lists are not appended, if all descriptor lists are empty then 'this' list is the single returned list

        Parameters:
        lists - multiple descriptor lists to be appended to this list.
        Returns:
        modified list of descriptors based on the provided input lists
